members.name: getCommand
members.comment: Gets the command that this CommandBlock will run when powered. This will never return null. If the CommandBlock does not have a command, an empty String will be returned instead.

return: Command that this CommandBlock will run when powered.

members.name: setCommand
members.comment: Sets the command that this CommandBlock will run when powered. Setting the command to null is the same as setting it to an empty String.

param: command - Command that this CommandBlock will run when powered.

members.name: getName
members.comment: Gets the name of this CommandBlock. The name is used with commands that this CommandBlock executes. This name will never be null, and by default is "@".

members.name: setName
members.comment: Sets the name of this CommandBlock. The name is used with commands that this CommandBlock executes. Setting the name to null is the same as setting it to "@".

name: org.bukkit.block.CommandBlock
comment: Represents a captured state of a command block.
